"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-nepal-wins-bronze-at-international-astronomy-olympiad-61-41.html\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Nov 19: Nepal has secured a bronze medal at the 29th International Astronomy Olympiad (IAO 2025), with Grade 10 student Sauryam Shrestha of St. Xavier's School, Godawari achieving the honor.  The competition was held in Dhaka, Bangladesh, from November 6 to 15, the Nepal Astronomical Society (NASO) reported.  Nepal has been participating in the prestigious global event for several years. According to NASO Chair Suresh Bhattarai, the country previously earned bronze medals in 2019 and 2023.  Participants for the international competition are selected through the National Astronomy Olympiad competition, an annual event organized since 2014. The national-level program aims to identify and nurture young scientific talent, with top performers chosen to represent Nepal internationally.  More than 3,000 students from across the nation have taken part in the National Astronomy Olympiad to date, many of whom are now pursuing higher studies in science at leading universities in Nepal and abroad. The competition is open to students from Grades 8 to 10-typically ages 13 to 20-from all seven provinces, with selection rounds held nationwide.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availab